comments: Booker (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Porzingis' (DAL) path and does not deliver contact on the pick.
Bridges (PHX) makes hand-on-ball contact to cleanly dislodge the incoming pass to Porzingis (DAL) prior to incidental contact occurring.
Porzingis (DAL) does not establish himself in Paul's (PHX) path when he makes contact that affects Paul's SQBR.
Booker (PHX) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Ayton (PHX) firms up and establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path during the pick.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contests Booker (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Brunson's (DAL) off-arm makes marginal contact with Crowder (PHX), which doesn't affect Crowder's ability to defend his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the cylinder and has a chance to score during Brunson's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Bullock (DAL) makes contact with Paul (PHX) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Porzingis (DAL) briefly grasps Bridges' (PHX) arm as both players engage during the incoming pass.
Bridges (PHX) makes hand-on-ball contact to dislodge the incoming pass from Porzingis (DAL).
Porzingis (DAL) and Bridges (PHX) both engage and then disengage in marginal arm contact. The contact does not affect Bridges' ability to gain possession of the loose ball.
